{"title_page": "List of proposed state mergers", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{For|proposed annexations of non-sovereign territories|List of irredentist claims or disputes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{more citations needed|date=April 2011}}\n{{original research|date=April 2011}}\n}}\nThis is a '''list of proposed state mergers''', including both current and historical proposals originating from sovereign states or organizations. The entities listed below differ from [[List of active separatist movements|separatist movements]] in that they would form as a merger or union of two or more existing [[Sovereign state|states]], [[Territory (country subdivision)|territories]], [[colony|colonies]] or other regions, becoming either a [[federation]], [[confederation]] or other type of unified [[sovereign state]].\n\n==Historic==\n\n===Until the 15th century===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"130\" | Proposed state\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"150\" | Components\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"70\" | Time period\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"80\" | Successful?\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"620\" | Notes\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag.svg}} [[Union of Hungary and Poland#Angevin Union|Angevin Union]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Hungary (1301-1382, rectangular).svg}} [[Kingdom of Hungary]]<br />{{flagicon image|Alex K Kingdom of Poland-flag.svg}} [[Kingdom of Poland (1025\u20131385)|Kingdom of Poland]] \n| 1370\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1370\u20131382)}}\n| See [[Union of Hungary and Poland]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag.svg}} [[Union of Hungary and Poland#Jagiellonian Union|Jagiellonian Union]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Hungary (15th century, rectangular).svg}} [[Kingdom of Hungary]]<br />{{flagicon image|Alex K Kingdom of Poland-flag.svg}} [[Kingdom of Poland (1385\u20131569)|Kingdom of Poland]] \n| 1440\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1440\u20131444)}}\n| See [[Union of Hungary and Poland]]\n|}\n\n===Early modern period===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"130\" | Proposed state\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"150\" | Components\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"70\" | Time period\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"80\" | Successful?\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"620\" | Notes\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Chor\u0105giew kr\u00f3lewska kr\u00f3la Zygmunta III Wazy.svg}} [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth]]\n| {{flagicon image|Alex K Kingdom of Poland-flag.svg}} [[Kingdom of Poland (1385\u20131569)]]<br />{{flagicon image|Alex K Grundwald flags 1410-03.svg}} [[Grand Duchy of Lithuania]]\n| 1569\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1569\u20131795)}}\n| See [[Union of Lublin]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag.svg}} [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian\u2013Muscovite Commonwealth]]\n| {{flagicon image|Chor\u0105giew kr\u00f3lewska kr\u00f3la Zygmunta III Wazy.svg}} [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Russia.svg}} [[Tsardom of Russia]]\n| 1574\u20131658\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| [[File:Estandarte Real de Felipe II.svg|20px]] [[Iberian Union]]\n| [[File:Coat of arms of Portugal (1640).svg|20px]] [[Kingdom of Portugal|Crown of Portugal]]<br /> [[File:Coat of Arms of the Crown of Castile (16th Century-1715).svg|20px]] [[Crown of Castille]] <br /> [[File:Escudo de Arag\u00f3n-Sicilia.svg|20px]] [[Crown of Aragon]]\n| 1580-1640\n| {{yes}}\n| Portugal became part of the realms of the [[Spanish Habsburg]] (Casa de Austria) following the death of [[Henry I of Portugal]] but resumed its independence 60 years later.\n|-\n| [[File:Coat of arms of the January Uprising.svg|20px]] [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian\u2013Ruthenian Commonwealth]]\n| {{flagicon image|Chor\u0105giew kr\u00f3lewska kr\u00f3la Zygmunta III Wazy.svg}} [[Polish\u2013Lithuanian Commonwealth]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Cossack Hetmanat.svg}} [[Cossack Hetmanate]]\n| 1658\u20131659\n| {{no}}\n| [[Treaty of Hadiach]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Union flag 1606 (Kings Colors).svg}} [[Kingdom of Great Britain]]\n| {{flag|Kingdom of England|England}}<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Scotland|Scotland}}\n| 1707\n| {{yes}}\n| Though having been ruled since 1603 in [[Personal Union]] when [[James VI]] succeeded both the [[Union of the Crowns|English and Scottish crowns]] both countries remained separate sovereign nations states until 1706 when the [[Treaty of Union]] unified them into a single entity.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Star-Spangled Banner flag.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Vermont Republic.svg}} [[Vermont Republic]]<br />{{flagicon image|Hopkinson Flag.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| 1777\u20131791\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Star-Spangled Banner flag.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| {{flag|Connecticut}}<br />{{flag|Delaware}}<br />{{flag|Georgia (U.S. state)|name=Georgia}}<br />{{flag|Maryland}}<br />{{flag|Massachusetts}}<br />{{flag|New Hampshire}}<br />{{flag|New Jersey}}<br />{{flag|New York}}<br />{{flag|North Carolina}}<br />{{flag|Pennsylvania}}<br />{{flag|Rhode Island}}<br />{{flag|South Carolina}}<br />{{flag|Virginia}}\n| 1786-1788\n| {{yes|Yes  <br /> (1788\u20131861)}}\n| [[United States Constitution]] is ratified by the [[Thirteen Colonies|Thirteen Original Colonies]], replacing the [[Articles of Confederation]] and thereby forming a Federal government, ending the individual sovereignty of the US States.\n|}\n\n===19th century===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"130\" | Proposed state\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"150\" | Components\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"70\" | Time period\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"80\" | Successful?\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"620\" | Notes\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the United Kingdom.svg}} [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland]]\n| {{flag|Kingdom of Great Britain|1606}}<br />{{flag|Kingdom of Ireland}}\n| 1800\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1801\u20131922)}}\n| Most of Ireland left the union as the [[Irish Free State]] in 1922.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Gran Colombia.svg}} [[Gran Colombia]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of New Granada (1814-1816).svg}} [[United Provinces of New Granada]]<br />{{flagicon image|Bandera de Angostura (20 de noviembre de 1817).svg}} [[Second Republic of Venezuela]]<br />{{flagicon image|Bandera de la Provincia Libre de Guayaquil.svg}} [[Royal Audiencia of Quito|Free Province of Guayaquil]]\n| 1819\u20131830\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1819\u20131830)}}\n| \n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Bandera del Primer Imperio Mexicano.svg}} [[First Mexican Empire]]\n| {{flagicon image|Bandera del Primer Imperio Mexicano.svg}} [[Mexico]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Spain (1785\u20131873, 1875\u20131931).svg}}[[Captaincy General of Guatemala]]\n| 1821\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1821\u20131823)}}\n| [[Central America]] was annexed into the [[First Mexican Empire]]. After the dissolution of the Empire only [[Chiapas]] choose to remain part of [[Mexico]], the rest became the [[Federal Republic of Central America]]. \nCosta Rica in particular was split between inner factions in favor and against the annexation ending in a [[Ochomogo War|Civil War]]. The pro-Mexican provinces declared membership but was not recognized by the pro-independence provinces.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Federal Republic of Central America.svg}} [[Federal Republic of Central America]]\n| {{flagicon image|Civil Flag of El Salvador.png}} [[El Salvador]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Honduras (1839-1866).svg}} [[Honduras]]<br />{{flagicon image|Zentralamerikanische Konf\u00f6deration 1823-1824.svg}} [[Nicaragua]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Guatemala (1825-1838).svg}} [[Guatemala]] <br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Los Altos.svg}} [[Los Altos, Central America|Los Altos]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1823-1824).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]\n| 1823\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1823\u20131839)}}\n| \n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1824-1840).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1824).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]<br /> {{flagicon image|Bandera de la Provincia de Guanacaste.svg}} [[Partido de Nicoya|Nicoya]]\n| 1824\n| {{yes}}\n|The old \"Partido de Nicoya\" currently encompasses most of the 21st-century [[Guanacaste Province]]. See [[Annexation of Nicoya]].\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Peru-Bolivian Confederation.svg}} [[Peru\u2013Bolivian Confederation]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Bolivia (1826-1851).svg}} [[Bolivia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Peru (1825 - 1950).svg}} [[Peru]]\n| 1829\u20131839\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1836\u20131839)}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|US flag 27 stars.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| {{flagicon image|US flag 26 stars.svg}} [[United States of America]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Texas.svg}} [[Republic of Texas]]\n| 1845\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| [[Texas annexation]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Italy (1861-1946).svg}} [[Kingdom of Italy]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Italy (1861-1946).svg}} [[Kingdom of Sardinia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Papal States (1808-1870).svg}} [[Papal States]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Grand Duchy of Tuscany (1840).svg}} [[Grand Duchy of Tuscany]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Duchy of Parma.svg}} [[Duchy of Parma]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Duchy of Modena.svg}} [[Duchy of Modena and Reggio]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Kingdom of the Two Sicilies (1816).svg}} [[Kingdom of the Two Sicilies]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Habsburg Monarchy.svg}} [[Kingdom of Lombardy\u2013Venetia]] (Part of [[Austrian Empire]])\n| 1848\u20131870\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| Although the Kingdom of Italy was proclaimed in 1861, the Italian Unification is generally considered to have been incomplete until after the integration of Venetia in 1866 and the capture of Rome in 1870. See [[Italian Unification]] and [[Expedition of the Thousand]].\n|-\n|{{flagicon image|Flag.svg}} Federation of Central America \n|{{flagicon image|Civil Flag of El Salvador.png}} [[El Salvador]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Honduras (1839-1866).svg}} [[Honduras]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Nicaragua (1852).svg}