r />{{flag|Kingdom of Romania}}\n| 1942\u20131944\n| {{no}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of SFR Yugoslavia.svg}} [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of SFR Yugoslavia.svg}} [[Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Albania 1946.svg}} [[People's Socialist Republic of Albania]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Bulgaria (1971-1990).svg}} [[People's Republic of Bulgaria]]\n| 1946\u20131948\n| {{no}}\n| [[Josip Broz Tito]] came extremely close to getting Albania into accepting integration into Yugoslavia, but relations cooled in 1948 over fears that Yugoslavia only intended to use Albania for raw materials, subsequently resulting in the expulsion of Yugoslav diplomats. Yugoslav/Bulgarian negotiations fell through when Moscow attempted to force both countries into accepting Soviet control over the merge, which caused Yugoslavia to withdraw from negotiations and precipitated the [[Tito\u2013Stalin split]].\n|-\n| {{flag|Dominion of India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon image|Drapeau Junagadh vector.svg}} [[Junagadh State]]\n| 1947\u20131948\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Annexation of Junagadh]]\n|-\n|{{flag|Dominion of India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon|British Raj}}[[List of princely states of British India (alphabetical)|Princely states]]\n| 1947\u20131950\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Instrument of Accession]]\n|-\n| {{flag|Dominion of Pakistan}}\n| {{flag|Pakistan}}<br />[[List of princely states of British India (alphabetical)|Princely states]]\n| 1947\u20131950\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Instrument of Accession]]\n|-\n|{{flag|Dominion of India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon image|Asafia flag of Hyderabad State.png}} [[Hyderabad State|Hyderabad]]\n| 1948\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Indian annexation of Hyderabad|Annexation of Hyderabad]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} Dominion of [[Canada]]\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} [[Canada|Dominion of Canada]]<br />{{flagicon image|Dominion of