sche Konf\u00f6deration 1823-1824.svg}} [[Nicaragua]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Guatemala (1825-1838).svg}} [[Guatemala]] <br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Los Altos.svg}} [[Los Altos, Central America|Los Altos]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1823-1824).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]\n| 1823\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1823\u20131839)}}\n| \n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1824-1840).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Costa Rica (1824).svg}} [[Costa Rica]]<br /> {{flagicon image|Bandera de la Provincia de Guanacaste.svg}} [[Partido de Nicoya|Nicoya]]\n| 1824\n| {{yes}}\n|The old \"Partido de Nicoya\" currently encompasses most of the 21st-century [[Guanacaste Province]]. See [[Annexation of Nicoya]].\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Peru-Bolivian Confederation.svg}} [[Peru\u2013Bolivian Confederation]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Bolivia (1826-1851).svg}} [[Bolivia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Peru (1825 - 1950).svg}} [[Peru]]\n| 1829\u20131839\n| {{yes|Yes <br /> (1836\u20131839)}}\n|\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|US flag 27 stars.svg}} [[United States of America]]\n| {{flagicon image|US flag 26 stars.svg}} [[United States of America]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Texas.svg}} [[Republic of Texas]]\n| 1845\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| [[Texas annexation]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Italy (1861-1946).svg}} [[Kingdom of Italy]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Italy (1861-1946).svg}} [[Kingdom of Sardinia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Papal States (1808-1870).svg}} [[Papal States]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Grand Duchy of Tuscany (1840).svg}} [[Grand Duchy of Tuscany]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Duchy of Parma.svg}} [[Duchy of Parma]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Duchy of Modena.svg}} [[Duchy of Modena and Reggio]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Kingdom of the Two Sicilies (1816).svg}} [[Kingdom of the Two Sicilies]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Habsburg Monarchy.svg}} [[Kingdom of Lombardy\u2013Venetia]] (Part of [[Austrian Empire]])\n| 1848\u20131870\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| Although the Kingdom of Italy was proclaimed in 1861, the Italian Unification is generally considered to have been incomplete until after the integration of Venetia in 1866 and the capture of Rome in 1870. See [[Italian Unification]] and [[Expedition of the Thousand]].\n|-\n|{{flagicon image|Flag.svg}} Federation of Central America \n|{{flagicon image|Civil Flag of El Salvador.png}} [[El Salvador]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Honduras (1839-1866).svg}} [[Honduras]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Nicaragua (1852).svg}} [[Nicaragua]]\n|1852\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n|Second attempt at unification that lasted for less than a month.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Liberia.svg}} [[Liberia]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Liberia.svg}} [[Liberia|Republic of Liberia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of the Republic of Maryland.svg}} [[Republic of Maryland]]\n| 1854-1857\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| Republic of Maryland was officially named Maryland in Liberia during its independence referendum on May 29, 1854.\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Confederate States of America (1861-1863).svg}} [[Confederate States of America]]\n| {{flagicon image|Fort Moultrie flag.svg}} [[South Carolina in the American Civil War|State of South Carolina]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Mississippi (1861-1894).svg}} [[Mississippi in the American Civil War|State of Mississippi]]<br />{{flagicon image|Florida Provisional 1861.svg}} [[Florida in the American Civil War|State of Florida]]<br />{{flagicon image|Alabama 1861 Obverse.svg}} [[Alabama in the American Civil War|State of Alabama]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Georgia non official.svg}} [[Georgia in the American Civil War|State of Georgia]]<br />{{flagicon image|Louisiana Feb 11 1861.svg}} [[Louisiana in the American Civil War|State of Louisiana]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Texas.svg}} [[Texas in the American Civil War|State of Texas]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Virginia (1861).svg}} [[Virginia in the American C