stan}}<br />[[List of princely states of British India (alphabetical)|Princely states]]\n| 1947\u20131950\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Instrument of Accession]]\n|-\n|{{flag|Dominion of India}}\n| {{flag|India}}<br />{{flagicon image|Asafia flag of Hyderabad State.png}} [[Hyderabad State|Hyderabad]]\n| 1948\n| {{yes}}\n| [[Indian annexation of Hyderabad|Annexation of Hyderabad]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} Dominion of [[Canada]]\n| {{flagicon image|Canadian Red Ensign 1921-1957.svg}} [[Canada|Dominion of Canada]]<br />{{flagicon image|Dominion of Newfoundland Red Ensign.svg}} [[Dominion of Newfoundland]]\n| 1949\n| {{yes|Yes}}\n| [[Newfoundland Act]]\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland (1953\u20131963).svg}} [[Federation of Rhodesia and Nyasaland]]\n| {{flag|Nyasaland|1963|name=Protectorate of Nyasaland}}<br />{{flag|Northern Rhodesia|1939-1953|name=Protectorate of Northern Rhodesia}}<br />{{flag|Southern Rhodesia|name=Colony of Southern Rhodesia}}\n| 1953\n| {{yes|Yes <br />(1953\u20131963)}}\n| A semi-independent state.\n|-\n| {{flagicon|United Kingdom}} [[United Kingdom]]\n| {{flag|United Kingdom}}<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Malta (1943-1964).svg}} [[Crown Colony of Malta]]\n| 1956\n| {{no|No}}\n| See [[1956 Maltese United Kingdom integration referendum]].\n|-\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of the North Borneo Federation.svg}} [[North Borneo Federation]]\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of North Borneo (1948\u20131963).svg}} [[Crown Colony of North Borneo]]<br />{{flagicon image|Flag of Sarawak (1946\u20131963).svg}} [[Crown Colony of Sarawak]]<br />{{flag|Brunei|1906|name=Protectorate of Brunei}}\n| 1956\u20131960\n| {{no}}\n| [[Sarawak]] and North Borneo (now known as [[Sabah]]) joined the Federation of Malaya several years later, a predecessor to modern [[Malaysia]], while [[Brunei]] reformed into an independent monarchy.\n|-\n| {{flag|West Indies Federation}}\n| {{flagicon image|Flag of Barbados (1870\u20131966).sv