uary 1999)|Lirim Kastrati]]|age={{Birth date and age|1999|1|16|df=y}}|caps=3|goals=0|club=[[NK Lokomotiva|Lokomotiva]]|clubnat=CRO|latest=v. {{fb|MNE}}, 14 October 2019<sup>'''U21'''</sup>}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=FW|name=[[Shkelqim Demhasaj]]|age={{Birth date and age|1996|4|19|df=y}}|caps=1|goals=0|club=[[FC Luzern|Luzern]]|clubnat=SUI|latest=v. {{fb|BUL}}, 10 June 2019}}\n{{nat fs r player|no=|pos=FW|name=[[Festim Alidema]]|age={{Birth date and age|1997|10|5|df=y}}|caps=0|goals=0|club=[[NK Slaven Belupo|Slaven Belupo]]|clubnat=CRO|latest=v. {{fb|MNE}}, 7 June 2019<sup>'''PRE'''</sup>}}\n{{nat fs end|background=244AA5|color=D0A650}}\n;Notes\n*<sup>'''INJ'''</sup> = Not part of the [[#Current squad|current squad]] due to injury.\n*<sup>'''U21'''</sup> = Was called up from national [[Kosovo national under-21 football team|U21]] squad.\n*<sup>'''PRE'''</sup> = Preliminary squad.\n\n==Personnel==\n[[File:Alg\u00e9rie - Arm\u00e9nie - 20140531 - Bernard Challandes.jpg|thumb|250px|[[Bernard Challandes]], the current manager of the Kosovo national football team.]]\n\n===Current technical staff===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=40% style=\"text-align:left;font-size:100%;\"\n|-\n!Position\n!Name\n|-\n|Head coach\n|{{flagicon|SUI}} {{sortname|Bernard|Challandes}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|Assistant coach(es)\n|-\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Ramush|Gashi|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Muharrem|Sahiti}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Genc|Hoxha|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|Fitness coach\n|{{flagicon|SUI}} {{sortname|Thomas|Richard|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|Goalkeeping coach\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Ahmet|Beselica|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Physiotherapist(s)\n|-\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Ismet|Shalaj|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Zheralldin|Durguti|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|Doctor\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Murat|Berisha|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|Device manager\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Sahit|Salihi|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|Team manager\n|{{flagicon|KVX}} {{sortname|Bajram|Shala|nolink=1}}\n|-\n|Technical director\n|{{flagicon|GER}} {{sortname|Michael|Nees}}\n|-\n|Video analyst\n|{{flagicon|GER}} {{sortname|Alexander|Carra|nolink=1}}\n|}\n\n==Kit suppliers==\nThe Kosovo kit has been mostly red and black before [[2008 Kosovo declaration of independence|declaration of independence]] with few changes throughout the years and after the independence the kits are mostly blue and yellow. On 5 October 2016, Kosovo signed with Spanish sportswear company [[Kelme (company)|Kelme]] to a four-year contract and was the first official kit suppliers of Kosovo after membership in UEFA and FIFA.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://telegrafi.com/nenshkruhet-marreveshja-mes-ffk-se-kelme-per-fanellat-e-perfaqesueses-se-kosoves-fotovideo/|title=N\u00ebnshkruhet marr\u00ebveshja mes FFK-s\u00eb dhe 'Kelme' p\u00ebr fanellat e P\u00ebrfaq\u00ebsueses s\u00eb Kosov\u00ebs (Foto/Video)|trans-title=Signed the agreement between FFK and 'Kelme' for the kits of Kosovo national football team (Photo/Video)|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|date=5 October 2016}}</ref> On 16 June 2018, Kosovo signed with Swiss sportswear company Fourteen to a four-year contract and becomes the current kit suppliers of Kosovo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ffk-kosova.com/2018/06/16/ffk-ja-promovoi-logon-e-re-dhe-sponsorin-e-ri-teknik/|title=FFK-ja promovoi logon e re dhe sponsorin e ri teknik|trans-title=FFK promoted the new logo and the new technical sponsor|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=16 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://telegrafi.com/zbulohen-fanellat-e-reja-te-kosoves-per-ligen-e-kombeve-dhe-logo-e-re-e-ffk-se/|title=Zbulohen fanellat e reja t\u00eb Kosov\u00ebs p\u00ebr Lig\u00ebn e Kombeve dhe logo e re e FFK-s\u00eb|trans-title=Revealed the new jersey of Kosovo for the Nations League and the new logo of FFK|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|date=16 June 2018}}</ref>\n{{Football kit box|width=5\n| pattern_la = _kosovo16h\n| pattern_b  = _kosovo16h\n| pattern_ra = _kosovo16h\n| pattern_sh =\n| pattern_so =\n| leftarm    = 0000FF\n| body       = 0000FF\n| rightarm   = 0000FF\n| shorts     = FFFF00\n| socks      = 0000FF\n| title      = Kosovo kit in the first<br />competitive match<br />against [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in<br />September 2016.}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Kit provider\n!Period\n!In matches against<!-- This comprises only for the permitted matches by FIFA that Kosovo played from 2014 to 2016, as there have been frequent changes of kit suppliers during that time -->\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Legea]]\n|align=\"center\"|2014\n|{{fb|HAI}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Puma (brand)|Puma]]\n|align=\"center\"|2014\n|{{fb|TUR}} and {{fb|SEN}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ITA}} [[Legea]]\n|align=\"center\"|2014\n|{{fb|OMA}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Umbro]]\n|align=\"center\"|2015\n|{{fb|EQG}} and {{fb|ALB}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Puma (brand)|Puma]]\n|align=\"center\"|2016\n|{{fb|FRO}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Kelme (company)|Kelme]]\n|align=\"center\"|2016\u20132018\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|SUI}} Fourteen\n|2018\u2013present\n|}\n\n==Stadiums==\nOn 12 July 2019, it was announced that a stadium will be built with a capacity of 30,000 seats.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://telegrafi.com/nis-ndertimi-stadiumit-nacional-te-kosoves/|title=Nis nd\u00ebrtimi i stadiumit nacional t\u00eb Kosov\u00ebs|date=12 July 2019|website=Telegrafi}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://telegrafi.com/prezantohet-projekti-per-stadiumin-kombetar-te-kosoves/|title=Prezantohet projekti p\u00ebr stadiumin Komb\u00ebtar t\u00eb Kosov\u00ebs|date=14 June 2019|website=Telegrafi}}</ref>\n{{updated|17 November 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=100% style=\"text-align:left;font-size:100%;\"\n!colspan=8 style=\"background: #244AA5; color: #D0A650;\"|Kosovo national football team home stadiums\n|-\n!{{abbr|Nr. of<br />matches|Number of matches}}\n!Image\n!Stadium\n!Capacity