 months|quote=All UEFA competitions and matches (including friendlies) for clubs and national teams for both men and women have been put on hold until further notice. The UEFA EURO 2020 play-off matches and international friendlies, scheduled for the end of March, will now be played in the international window at the start of June, subject to a review of the situation|publisher=[[UEFA]]|date=17 March 2020}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote2|d|After stadiums in [[Adem Jashari Olympic Stadium|Mitrovica]] and [[Fadil Vokrri Stadium|Pristina]] were under renovation and do not meet UEFA standards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegrafi.com/keto-jane-11-stadiumet-e-superliges-dhe-asnjeri-nuk-ploteson-kushtet-foto/|title=K\u00ebto jan\u00eb 11 stadiumet e Superlig\u00ebs dhe asnj\u00ebri nuk i plot\u00ebson kushtet (Foto)|trans-title=These are the 11 Superleague stadiums and none meet the conditions (Photo)|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|date=3 May 2016}}</ref> Kosovo played the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification&nbsp;\u2013 UEFA Group I#Matches|qualifying matches]] of the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Loro Bori\u00e7i Stadium]] ({{lang-sq|Stadiumi Loro Bori\u00e7i}}), a multi-use stadium in [[Shkod\u00ebr]], [[Albania]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtklive.com/sq/news-single.php?ID=83148|title=Loro Bori\u00e7i, sht\u00ebpia e p\u00ebrkohshme e Kosov\u00ebs|trans-title=Loro Bori\u00e7i, the temporary home of Kosovo|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Radio Television of Kosovo]]|date=28 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/edirama.al/posts/10153918522541523|title=Loro Bori\u00e7i, i rilindur gati p\u00ebr kolaudim (Foto)|trans-title=Loro Bori\u00e7i, reborn ready for test (Photo)|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Edi Rama]]|website=[[Facebook]]|date=11 August 2016}}</ref>}}\n{{Cnote2 End}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.ffk-kosova.com/}} {{in lang|sq|en}}\n*[http://www.national-football-teams.com/country/259/Kosovo.html Kosovo] at National Football Teams\n*[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesk/kosovo-intres.html Kosovo] at [[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]]\n\n{{Football in Kosovo}}\n{{National sports teams of Kosovo}}\n{{UEFA teams}}\n\n[[Category:Kosovo national football team]]\n[[Category:European national association football teams]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the men's team|the women's team|Kosovo women's national football team}}\n{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox national football team\n| Name                     = Kosovo\n| Nickname                 = {{nowrap|{{lang|sq|Dardan\u00ebt}} (''Dardanians'')}}\n| Badge                    = \n| Badge_size               = \n| Association              = ''[[Football Federation of Kosovo|Federata e Futbollit e Kosov\u00ebs]]'' (FFK)\n| Confederation            = [[UEFA]] (Europe)\n| Coach                    = {{sortname|Bernard|Challandes}}\n| Captain                  = {{sortname|Amir|Rrahmani}}\n| Most caps                = {{sortname|Amir|Rrahmani}} (29)\n| Top scorer               = {{sortname|Vedat|Muriqi}} (8)\n| Home Stadium             = [[Fadil Vokrri Stadium]]\n| FIFA Trigramme           = <!--FIFA use KVX so do not remove it or you risk being reverted-->KVX<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dryomin|first1=Mark|last2=Tabeira|first2=Martin|last3=Lozano|first3=Carles|last4=Jeffree|first4=Iain|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/fifa-codes.html|title=FIFA Country Codes|quote=Kosovo (KVX)|website=rsssf.com|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref>\n| pattern_la1              = _yellowborder\n| pattern_b1               = _kosovo18h\n| pattern_ra1              = _yellowborder\n| pattern_sh1              = _kos18ht\n| pattern_so1              = _kos18h\n| leftarm1                 = 0321C6\n| body1                    = 0321C6\n| rightarm1                = 0321C6\n| shorts1                  = 0321C6\n| socks1                   = FFFF00\n| pattern_la2              = _kosovo18a\n| pa